To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

The following information about City of Seattle job listings posted between 1/1/20 and the date this request is processed: Department, Job Title, Date Posted, Whether the Posting is Active/Filled/Closed, Date Filled/Closed (if applicable). If possible, please also include the job requirements.

I would appreciate it if you could provide the records in Excel or CSV format, or the native electronic format if unavailable.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Rose Terse

Dear FBI:

This is a request for records under the Freedom of Information Act.

RECORDS REQUESTED

I request all records related to Barbara Howar. Howar was born in Nashville, Tennessee, USA on September 27, 1934 and died on August 2, 2024.

OTHER NAMES USED

The subject was born Barbara Stephanye Dearing.

PROOF OF DEATH

I have attached Ms. Howar’s news obituary from the Washington Post.

FEES

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes. If you decide to charge me fees, please let me know in advance if those fees will exceed $25.

FORM OF PRODUCTION

I would prefer that you fulfill this request electronically, producing responsive records via email attachment if available or on CD-ROM if not.

CONCLUSION

Thank you for responding to this request.

Sincerely,

Nicholas Marritz
